Insurance Release Notes

Customize the Expense Item Form to Enhance Usability
Claims adjusters can process expenses more efficiently by using forms that show only the attributes specific to coverage in the expense line item form.

Customize Optional Coverage Rule Selections Based on User Profiles
Automatically select Required Coverage or Default Selected optional coverage rules for users based on their user profile.

Display Attribute Messages Based on User Profiles
Show users product attribute messages based on their user profile.

Display Optional Coverage Rule Messages Based on User Profiles
Show users optional coverage validation rule messages based on their user profile.

Enhanced User Experience and Performance for Policy Terms Standing
The Policy Terms Standing card has been enhanced to show policy terms separately in Policy Details and Coverage Details sections.

Hide Attributes or Attribute Values Based on User Profiles
Hide product attributes or attribute values from users based on their user profile.

Set Attribute Required Field Validation for Claim Product Models
You can now set the Required field indicator on attributes for Claim Involved Injury and Claim Damaged Property record types.

Show Optional Coverages Based on User Profiles
Control which users can see optional coverages with profile-based eligibility rules.

Upload and View the Plan Coverage Details of Members for Enrollment
Upload group benefits coverage selections of members and view the coverage selections for each member in the user interface by using the Enrollment Census Lightning web component.

Services for Insurance Summer '23
Explore updates to existing services in Summer '23.
Data Model Updates for Insurance FSC Summer '23
Explore the new data model object for this release.
title: Insurance Product Customization and Policy Management
